16/08/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- State Department spokesman Sean McCormack urged the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) on Tuesday (15 August) to lay down its arms and cease terrorist attacks against Turkey. The statement marked the 22nd anniversary of the armed campaign by PKK, which has claimed over 30,000 lives. 
Also Tuesday, another bomb exploded in Istanbul's historic quarter of Sultanahmet, the second in as many days. No one was injured in this one. 
In other news, the army announced that two Turkish soldiers were killed in clashes with PKK terrorists in the southeast Sirnak province Monday. Security forces have been conducting a large operation against the PKK in the region. (Sabah - 16/08/06; US State Department, Zaman - 15/08/06)
